229
00:13:24,519 --> 00:13:27,636
I heard she's pushing 40
and everything's fake.

230
00:13:28,479 --> 00:13:31,710
Yeah, I started that rumor.

231
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:36,994
Since we agree on the delivery system for
the message, maybe we should talk about...

232
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:38,513
...what the message could be.

233
00:13:38,679 --> 00:13:41,147
Well, I think we should show
what Earthlings look like.

234
00:13:41,319 --> 00:13:44,948
The plaque they sent on the Pioneer probe
had a drawing of a naked man and woman.

235
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:46,394
Yeah, I never cared for that.

236
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:52,635
It's advertising to predator races
just how soft and squishy we are.

237
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:53,869
Squeeze yourself.

238
00:13:54,039 --> 00:13:55,631
Oh, don't be offended.

239
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:59,076
You know of the four of us,
you have the most veal-like consistency.

240
00:14:01,160 --> 00:14:05,551
Maybe we can appear non-aggressive,
but also protect ourselves if necessary.

241
00:14:05,719 --> 00:14:07,949
Like smiling and waving with one hand...

242
00:14:08,120 --> 00:14:11,157
...but the other hand
holding the severed head of a tiger.

243
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:15,315
You wanna send a passive-aggressive
message into space? That's ridiculous.

244
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,948
Oh, you mean passive-aggressive
like posting pictures...

245
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:22,511
...of you and your wife eating cosmopolitan
balls that you know belong in my mouth?

246
00:14:24,759 --> 00:14:28,752
Maybe Howard meant passive-aggressive
like asking our group's help...

247
00:14:28,920 --> 00:14:30,592
...and then only choosing Leonard.

248
00:14:31,079 --> 00:14:33,309
Look, I'm sorry I hurt your feelings...

249
00:14:33,519 --> 00:14:37,558
...but you two have strong personalities
and always end up taking over.

250
00:14:37,719 --> 00:14:38,834
It's not always.

251
00:14:38,999 --> 00:14:41,957
What about when we went to Comic-Con
dressed like Jabba the Hutt?

252
00:14:42,159 --> 00:14:46,277
You got to be Jabba's head
and I got to be his fat slug butt.

253
00:14:47,840 --> 00:14:49,910
We looked great.

254
00:14:50,680 --> 00:14:52,511
You let a guy sit on me.

255
00:14:52,999 --> 00:14:55,957
He was dressed as Princess Leia.
It made a nice picture.

256
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:01,272
I'm just saying,
sometimes Raj and lfeel pushed aside.

257
00:15:01,439 --> 00:15:05,068
Yeah, like when you took Sheldon to Texas
and showed him all around NASA.

258
00:15:05,239 --> 00:15:07,230
You didn't even think
to ask me and Leonard.

259
00:15:07,879 --> 00:15:09,392
You know what? You're right.

260
00:15:09,599 --> 00:15:10,827
lshould've asked you.

261
00:15:10,999 --> 00:15:14,594
And if he does ask you, go, it's amazing.

262
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:20,477
If we're talking about being left out, you
guys went to Skywalker Ranch without us.

263
00:15:20,639 --> 00:15:24,029
Oh, I recommend that too.
That was a magical experience.

264
00:15:24,799 --> 00:15:28,838
Wait. Sheldon spent a whole day with
James Earl Jones and never told any of us.

265
00:15:29,159 --> 00:15:32,037
I sure did. Oh, my goodness.

266
00:15:32,199 --> 00:15:35,157
From Jabba's head
to ice cream with Darth Vader.

267
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:37,151
I'm having a heck of a ride.

268
00:15:38,519 --> 00:15:41,272
Clearly, good things happen
when I'm in charge.

269
00:15:41,439 --> 00:15:45,318
Now, why don't you boys step aside?
Let me knock this project out.

270
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:47,835
Sheldon, you're not in charge.
Raj is in charge.

271
00:15:47,999 --> 00:15:50,229
Leonard, who's really in charge?

272
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:54,916
The person in charge
or those who put him in charge?

273
00:15:55,399 --> 00:15:58,357
He's right.
If you think about it, we're all in charge.

274
00:15:58,520 --> 00:16:02,433
No, the guy in charge is in cha--
Why's everyone so bad at these?

275
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:07,635
I mean, the whole experience reminded me
about how much I hated that world.

276
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:10,439
You know, the anxiety, the depression,
the negativity.

277
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:12,033
I don't wanna feel those things.

278
00:16:12,199 --> 00:16:15,509
I wanna sell drugs to people
who feel those things.

279
00:16:16,519 --> 00:16:20,148
I can't believe you got up and walked out
of an audition for a big movie.

280
00:16:20,319 --> 00:16:23,709
I did. I mean, I walked in, read for the part,
then stunk up the place.

281
00:16:23,920 --> 00:16:25,353
But then I walked right out.

282
00:16:27,159 --> 00:16:29,434
I'm glad you have a new appreciation
for yourjob.

283
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:33,149
I do. And I don't think I've ever thanked you
properly for helping me get it.

284
00:16:33,639 --> 00:16:37,871
"Properly," "at all,"
it's just words I've never heard.

285
00:16:38,039 --> 00:16:40,951
Well, thank you. You're
a good friend and you changed my life.

286
00:16:41,120 --> 00:16:43,873
You're welcome. Hey,
now that you're making some real money...

287
00:16:44,079 --> 00:16:47,310
...maybe you could take your friend out
for a nice thank-you dinner.

288
00:16:47,639 --> 00:16:50,107
-Sure.
-You have to invite your other friend...

289
00:16:50,279 --> 00:16:54,033
...because she overheard you talking
and it would be awkward to exclude her.

290
00:16:54,999 --> 00:16:56,830
-Okay.
-How about now?

291
00:16:57,920 --> 00:16:58,909
All right.

292
00:17:01,639 --> 00:17:03,197
Don't forget your wallet.

293
00:17:12,799 --> 00:17:15,393
Greetings from planet Earth.

294
00:17:16,559 --> 00:17:20,154
Just turn left at Alpha Centauri,
you can't miss it.

295
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:24,234
[IN ALIEN LANGUAGE]

296
00:17:57,999 --> 00:17:59,910
